  "title": "Accountant (Group Reporting, Shipping / Marine Industry)",
  "description": "<ul><li><li><p>Review subsidiaries’ management accounts</p></li><li><p>Prepare group consolidation reports</p></li><li><p>Perform intercompany reconciliations, eliminations and adjustments</p></li><li><p>Provide financial analysis, variance explanations and insights</p></li><li><p>Review and approve transactions within ERP workflows</p></li><li><p>Prepare and submit GST returns</p></li><li><p>Liaise with external auditors and manage audit timelines</p></li><li><p>Draft financial statements and notes to accounts</p></li><li><p>Support statutory filings and annual returns</p></li><li><p>Assist in corporate tax schedules and respond to tax queries</p></li><li><p>Support system implementation and process improvements</p></li><li><p>Perform ad-hoc duties as required</p></li></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong><br /></p><ul><li><p>Degree in Accounting or related discipline</p></li><li><p>Minimum 5 years’ experience handling full sets of accounts for multiple entities</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of accounting standards and statutory reporting</p></li><li><p>Experience in group consolidation and audit coordination</p></li><li><p>ERP system experience preferred (e.g. Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central)</p></li><li><p>Strong analytical, organizational and time-management skills</p></li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Interested applicants for the above advertised position(s), please kindly email an updated copy of your resume to: <strong>gs1@talenttradersg.com</strong></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p>EA License No.: 13C6305</p><p><br /></p><p>Reg. No.: R23117344 (Tiong Tian Ho)</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p>For candidate who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>",
